Acq_10
Initialization error!

CAUSE:

  1. Not enough memory to load necessary dll files

SOLUTION:

  1. Make sure that there is enough RAM on the acquisition computer (see the minimum computer system requirements).

  2. Reinstall the drivers of the unit on the computer.

  3. Close external applications and try again.

Acq_11
Operating System error:

CAUSE:

  1. Current user does not have the permission to write the logs on the computer

SOLUTION:

  1. Make sure that the current user has full permissions on C:\ProgramData\TW

Acq_20
Bad or Corrupted Unit Driver Installation

CAUSE:

  1. Missing or corrupted installation files: the drivers and the firmwares of the unit are not in the same folder

SOLUTION:

  1. Remove the drivers installation folder.

  2. Reinstall the drivers of the unit on the computer.

Acq_25
Impossible to Get Unit System Settings

CAUSE:

  1. Communication between the computer and the unit has been lost

SOLUTION:

  1. Check the ethernet cables. Replace the cables if needed.

  2. Check the ethernet coupler. Replace it if needed.

  3. Check the CJ898 switch ethernet board. Replace it if needed.

  4. Update the drivers of the computer ethernet board. Replace it if needed.

  5. Check the CAN bus cables. Replace the cables if needed.

Acq_36

SOLUTION:

  1. Make sure that the computer is compliant with the minimum computer system requirements of the unit. If not, add RAM to the computer.

  2. Close external applications and try again.

Acq_50
Incorrect driver installation

CAUSE:

  1. The drivers installed in the acquisition computer don't match the equipment currently connected to the computer or not equipment at all connected to the computer

SOLUTION:

  1. If the unit has two sensors, one of the two sensors is not yet ready to start the acquisition. Wait at least one minute for the communication to be established and try again.

  2. Uninstall the drivers and reinstall the drivers corresponding to the equipment currently connected to the computer

  3. Check the network cables connected to the unit.

  4. Connect the equipment to the computer

Acq_68
The network board bandwidth is too low to launch an acquisition.

CAUSE:

  1. The network board connected to the unit is not capable or configured to reach the required bandwith ( 1 Gbit/s)

SOLUTION:

Acq_70
Timeout on image reception

CAUSE:

  1. Time between the X-Ray emission and the image reception is higher than 2 seconds.

SOLUTION:

  1. Check the network topology (switch, HUB, cable distance...).

  2. Check that there is no virus on the computer.

  3. Check the computer configuration.

  4. Check the cable connected between the CJ855 generator power board and the sensor control board. Replace it if needed.

CEPHGANTRY_12800
Power supply 5V is out of range (P5VAN)

CAUSE:

  1. Cable CPB12 between the CJ901 ceph step motor board and the CJ856 motor board is defective.

  2. CJ848, CJ901 or CJ856 is defective.

  3. Defective power supply.

SOLUTION:

  1. Switch the unit ON and make sure that stop switch is released.

  2. Check cable CPB12 between CJ901/J1 and CJ856/J14 & J10. Replace it if needed.

  3. Replace the CJ848 ceph microprocessor board.

  4. Replace the CJ901 ceph step motor board.

  5. Replace the CJ856 motor board.

CEPHGANTRY_25378
Unable to determine secondary collimator position

CAUSE:

  1. Secondary collimator position feedback is wrong:

  2. Potentiometer cable is disconnected or defective.

  3. Defective potentiometer.

  4. Bad detection on the potentiometer.

  5. Faulty component on CJ848 or CJ901 boards.

SOLUTION:

  1. Verify and plug the cable to connector J5 on CJ901.

  2. Make sure the pressure ball is making correct contact with the potentiometer track. If the potentiometer track is damaged, replace it.

  3. Change the cable from CJ901/J5 to CJ904/J2.

  4. Change the CJ901 ceph step motor board.

  5. Change the ceph CJ848 microprocessor board.

CEPHGANTRY_25382
Sensor position detector (measurement error greater than limit)

CAUSE:

  1. Unexpected sensor position.

SOLUTION:

  1. Restart the calibration. If the problem continues:

SENSOR_65312
Mismatch between encoder/potentiometer on rotation position measurement

CAUSE:

  1. Cable 91 (for 3D units) or cable 43 (for 2D units) is defective.

  2. Faulty R position measurement.

  3. R encoder cable is disconnected or defective.

  4. R optical encoder is defective.

  5. Faulty component on the CJ856 motor board or the CJ848 microprocessor board.

  6. Faulty R encoder track.

SOLUTION:

  1. Run the Rotation calibration

  2. Check and replace if needed cable 91 (for 3D units) or cable 43 (for 2D units) going from CJ856/J11 to the sensor control board. Have especially carefully a look at the pin#4 of this cable on the CJ856 motor board side. If this pin seems to be too opened, repair it or replace the cable included in the rotation cable kit.

    1. Check the R potentiometer:

    2. Verify cable 35 on both sides (J5 on the CJ856 motor board and J2 on the CJ858 rotation detector board).

    3. Run the effective range estimation diagnostics a few times for the rotation using the Service Tools.

    4. Check potentiometer feedback with a multimeter and change the cable if needed.

    1. Check the R optical encoder:

    2. Verify cable 45 on both sides (J12 on the CJ856 motor board and J1 on CJ857 (or CJ917 depending of the SN of the unit) movement detector board).

    3. Check if LEDs LD3 and LD4 are blinking on the CJ856 motor board when the arm is rotated manually.

    4. Check voltages with a multimeter and change the cable or the CJ857 movement detector board if needed.

  5. Change the CJ856 motor board.

  6. Change the motor microprocessor CJ848 board.

  7. Change the motion assembly.
